reviews.text:
Small cute station with just 2 platforms. Platform 1 brings you to Wool from London Waterloo and platform 2 takes you back from Wool to London Waterloo.

Has toilets operating till 5pm. Just outside the station there's taxi services and Wool bus station where you can board X54 to Durdledoor.

Lovely..
Few buses per day,
from Weymouth to poole and around.
Nice little station can be busy at times trains run on time.

Worn out and lacking faciltys. Ticket machines are on one platform only. Toilets never seem to be open which is always appreciated when the train doesn't come. Ticket office has a limted opening which begs the question why bother. And very little shelter from the element's so expect to be cold and wet in winter.

This is a housing village with no redeeming features. The level crossing is the slowest thing ever, and it chops the traffic off for up to 15 minutes at a time, and sometimes it operates up to 4 times an hour! The train station is a prefabricated mess, which is sometimes open, but more often than not, closed. The best thing about this place is the road out of here!
